how do u teach kids values both my girls are now we live in a wealthy town near chicago and everyone around us are quite wealthy also my children dont know the value of things they wont share w other classmates wont give away things its terrible the life i live is very privaledge and i dont want them acting like spoiled little girls when there older what should i do stop giving them everything they ask for and stand behind your decision even if they throw tantrums let them see you interact kindly and generously with those around you and follow your example encourage them to donate clothes and toys to those less fortunate than them and for their birthdays and holidays let them help you choose charitable gifts to give as well as gifts to family and friends involve them in chores and running the house even if it's things as simple as picking up their room or setting the table for this you might find a website like handipoints com helpful where you can track the chores that children do and let them earn points towards rewards for gifts or activities finally check out other online resources where other parents talk about teaching kids values here's a set of posts from the mommy points blog where mother of seven chris talks about instilling values in her kids http www handipoints com mommypoints cat Friends Azumanga Daioh W.I.T.C.H. Animal Crossing Our Gang Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Shaggy dog story Care Bears The Apprentice 2 Theory of conduct Gift economy Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Infantilism Gender role Recurring South Park characters Cardcaptor Sakura Hilary Duff Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Doug Autism Garfield Charmed Economics About a Boy Jam (TV series) The Fairly OddParents Dog training Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Divorce The Addams Family Saint Nicholas The Jeffersons (South Park) Expert system The Critic Child sexuality New 